    <p>The fifth ses­sion of a sto­ry­telling se­ries fea­tur­ing lo­cal folk tales by Gate­way Theatre. This is a story of a mouse deer called Sang Kan­cil, who longs to eat from the fruit trees across the river. But the river is filled with croc­o­diles wait­ing to de­vour Sang Kan­cil and he will need his wits to get across. Gate­way Theatre sup­ports made-in-Sin­ga­pore works and pro­motes pos­i­tive mes­sages and so­cial val­ues to chil­dren, youth and fam­i­lies.</p>
    <p>To­mor­row, 11am</p>
    <p>Free with reg­is­tra­tion bit.ly/34I8m8F un­der­stand the key el­e­ments of fic­tion writ­ing, in­clud­ing story struc­ture, char­ac­ter­i­sa­tion and story set­ting. Or­gan­ised by GlowWorm, which runs work­shops fo­cused on 21st-cen­tury es­sen­tial skills such as cre­ativ­ity, com­mu­ni­ca­tion and col­lab­o­ra­tion. Sept 5, 7, 9 & 11</p>
    <p>$130 bit.ly/3hJU9ve</p>


